main event: An illuminated star-like object was observed through binoculars while taking radar recordings on March 8, 1963.
interesting points: The object moved at a constant speed and disappeared to the E/SE., The observation lasted approximately 5 minutes., The sighting was conducted under normal dusk light conditions., The object was evaluated as a probable satellite by the evaluating officer., No physical evidence was obtained from the sighting.
witness description: LT Parks USN, LTJG Howse USN, LT Akers USN, all reliable and attached to USS Sculpin.
